[normal]The Society of Biology is a core mem
[normal]ber of the 
[normal]Drug Discovery Pathways Group
[normal], an informal partnership that seeks to address these issues by 
[normal]establishing a networked community of skilled researchers to help revitalise the UK pharmaceutical sector. The group
[normal] [bold]focusses on three main areas;
[normal] [bold]industry-academia
[normal] [bold]partnerships
[normal], [bold]knowledge
[normal] [bold]and
[normal] [bold]skills, with around
[normal] [bold]20 learned societies and professional bodies involved in specific activities and work streams.
